  <hr/>
  <p><strong>William Faulkner:</strong>A good psychologist certainly could or he would be a bad psychologist if
                    he couldn't. <span class="event tooltip" title="There was some audience laughter happening">[audience laughter]</span> I think that&#x2014;that one
                    reads a book from the same jumping off place that one writes a book, that one
                    reads a book from his own background of&#x2014;of observation, imagination,
                    and experience, too.  That no one man can put into a book what a dozen men
                    can&#x2014;can read into it.</p>
  <hr/>
  <p><strong>Unidentified participant:</strong>But don't you think artistic control keeps the psychologist from
                        analyzing the writing </p>
