  <hr/>
  <p><strong>William Faulkner:</strong>Only, in primitive peoples&#x2014;I mean by primitive peoples
                    a&#x2014;a small group which are obsolete inside another
                    culture&#x2014;the&#x2014;the distance between what is humor and what is
                    tragic is never very great, that it&#x2014;it may be&#x2014;be funny now
                    but you better watch out. That was simply that&#x2014;that the same
